---
import CodeSnippet from '@/components/CodeSnippet.astro';
import {
  CANONICAL_METHODS,
  METHODS_IN_ORDER,
} from '@/components/react/canonical-methods';
---

<section class="border-t border-border py-12 sm:py-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
    <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">
      How it actually works
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
      Eleven ways to find the canonical
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-muted-foreground">
      Stripping <code>/amp</code> from a URL gets you the right answer
      roughly half the time. The other half it produces broken links,
      wrong articles, or 404s — different sites bury the canonical in
      different places, and there's no single tag we can rely on. So
      AmputatorBot tries each of these in priority order, and falls
      through to the next when one doesn't match. The result you get back
      tells you exactly which one succeeded.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-muted-foreground">
      The last one,{' '}
      <strong class="text-foreground">guess-and-check</strong>, is the
      interesting one: when nothing on the page tells us what the
      canonical is, we strip the AMP markers, fetch the resulting page,
      and compare its article text to the AMP page's article text. If
      they're similar enough, we trust the guess. If not, we return
      nothing — better no answer than a wrong one.
    </p>
  </div>

  <ol class="mx-auto mt-8 grid max-w-5xl gap-4 px-4 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:px-6">
    {
      METHODS_IN_ORDER.map((key, idx) => {
        const m = CANONICAL_METHODS[key];
        return (
          <li class="flex flex-col rounded-md border border-border bg-card p-5">
            <p class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground">
                {String(idx + 1).padStart(2, '0')}
              </span>
              <span class="font-medium text-foreground">{m.label}</span>
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">{m.summary}</p>
            {m.snippet ? (
              <CodeSnippet
                class="mt-3"
                code={m.snippet}
                language={m.snippetLanguage}
              />
            ) : null}
          </li>
        );
      })
    }
  </ol>
</section>
